<h2 class=3D"eplus-wrapper wp-block-heading" id=3D"0-what-are-mixed-numbers=
">What are Mixed Numbers?</h2>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper">A mixed number is a <a href=3D"https://www.spla=
shlearn.com/math-vocabulary/number-sense/whole-numbers" target=3D"_blank" r=
el=3D"noreferrer noopener">whole number</a>, and a proper <a href=3D"https:=
//www.splashlearn.com/math-vocabulary/fractions/fraction" target=3D"_blank"=
 rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">fraction</a> represented together.&nbsp; It ge=
nerally represents a number between any two whole numbers.&nbsp;</p>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper">Look at the given image, it represents a fracti=
on that is <a href=3D"https://www.splashlearn.com/math-vocabulary/number-se=
nse/greater-than" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" title=3D"">greater tha=
n</a> 1 but <a href=3D"https://www.splashlearn.com/math-vocabulary/counting=
-and-comparison/less-than" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" title=3D"">le=
ss than</a> 2. It is thus, a mixed number.&nbsp;</p>



